ether other companies have similar problems=E2=80=94they almost certainly d=
o. The question is whether the industry will learn from Meta's failure or s=
imply get better at hiding it.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb=
(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">The continued refusal to rel=
ease their updated guidelines suggests Meta, at least, hasn't learned the l=
esson. To all appearances, they=E2=80=99re still treating this as a PR prob=
lem rather than an engineering challenge. Until that changes=E2=80=94until =
